author: mrglavas
msg: Fixing some subtle bugs. Should only be trimming XML spaces off of a value. Use XMLChar.trim() instead of String.trim() (which trims off all sorts of non-XML space characters).

author: mrglavas
msg: Fixing subtle bugs with string tokenization. The regex "\\s+" matches a couple characters (0xB and 0xC) which are not XML white spaces. Use a StringTokenizer instead with the four white spaces chars (0x9, 0xA, 0xD, 0x20) as delimiters. Should be slightly faster too since the split() method ends up compiling a Pattern every time you call it.
